Product description

Just like its name implies, the New House Kitchen Electric Griddle & Crepe Maker is a master when it comes to doing double-duty. This Crepe maker has a powerful 1200 watt heating element that heats up your Crepe pan quickly, while precise temperature knob makes it easy to make your breakfast exactly how you want it. Includes wooden batter spreader and spatula for perfect distribution, giving you precise results every time. Take advantage of the large non-stick surface to cook a variety of foods at once and have a meal in minutes. This non-stick surface is easy to clean and maintain - gently wipe down the surface with a damp cloth until food residue is removed. With the New House Kitchen Electric Griddle & Crepe Maker, you can savor the entire cooking process as much as the end results!

Tom Steele
TOP 500 REVIEWERVINE VOICE
5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to use - easy to clean!
February 28, 2019
Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
My wife and I went to Paris for vacation a few years back. One of our favorite treats was a corner crepe stand near our hotel. We would be out all day and take the Metro back to our hotel and the crepe wagon was one block from our hotel. It was in April and it was cold and the hot nutella filled crepes were delicious.

Fast forward to today and I am on Amazon where I see the reasonably priced New House Kitchen Electric Griddle & Crepe Maker Precise Temperature Control 12" Non-Stick Grill Pan and decided to try it. Upon arrival, we searched for crepe recipes and found a Martha Stewart crepe recipe that was easy to make and we had all the required ingredients so we gave it a go.

Mine weren't as pretty as the crepes we remembered so fondly in Paris, but I was impressed with the New House Crepe maker. Even my daughter was able to make her own crepe. I'll post the recipe at the end of the review...

But first, let's talk about the New House Crepe maker. It is very, very easy to use. Just plug it in and set it halfway between light and dark. Mix your favorite crepe batter recipe and pour about 1/2 cup onto the middle of the griddle. Use the provided wood tool to LIGHTLY spin in a circle making a (sort of) round shape in the middle of the griddle. You want it as thin as possible.

After cooking for about 1 1/2 minutes, you flip it and cook a minute on the other side and slather some nutella on it and fold it into quarters, plate and serve.

The crepe maker heats up quickly. If you make a mess, like we did, it cleans easily. I found it easiest to let any mistakes just continue to cook and then they come off the non-stick surface very easily - making cleanup a cinch.

That's really all there is to it. Our machine works great without any hot spots or burning. It couldn't be any easy, except the part where we aren't the best at making circles. LOL

I would say this is a five star crepe maker. There are probably better ones out there, but I'm ignorant of them or how they would be better. This is a great basic unit.

The recipe we used was very easy.

1 cup all-purpose flour (spooned and leveled)
1 tablespoon sugar
1/4 teaspoon coarse salt
1 1/2 cups whole milk
4 large eggs
3 tablespoons unsalted butter, melted

Mix it all together into a smooth liquid and pour about 1/2 cup in the center of the crepe maker and prepare as described above.

I hope this is a helpful review. If there is anything more you would like to know, please ask. I try to check my reviews for comments and respond to them right away. I think it is important for fellow shoppers on Amazon to look out for one another by letting each other know if a product is good, or if it is a stinker. I take this very seriously and try to be helpful. Thank you!
